            },
            "answer_text": "Quite difficult. Let me sum it up by paraphrasing one of my PDEs professors: Derivatives are easy. Integrals are hard. [Nonlinear] ODEs are so hard, if we can reduce them to an integral (even if we can\u2019t evaluate that integral), we typically call that a success. PDEs are so hard, if we can reduce them to an ODE [or system thereof], we typically call that a success, even if we can\u2019t solve the ODE. ",
