            "answer_text": "How difficult is partial differential equations? In general, linear ordinary differential equations are easy, non-linear ordinary differential equations are often hard. Similarly with partial differential equations. Only the simplest cases have been solved in closed form. Understanding the idea behind these equations is straightforward. Solving the harder cases is usually done by computer intensive methods. ",
